      <div class="g-plusone" data-size="medium" style="margin-left:10px;"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="clear-block clear">&nbsp;</div>
  
  <div class="content"><p><strong>UPDATE: BTC has rallied 26% off its lows in the last 55 minutes</strong> - with extreme volumes</p>
<p><img alt="" src="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user3303/imageroot/2013/11/20131201_BTC2.jpg" style="width: 599px; height: 555px;" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>From it&#39;s <a href="http://www.zerohedge.com/news/2013-11-29/bitcoin-now-worth-more-gold">gold-matching highs at $1242 on Thursday night</a>, the price of <strong>Bitcoin has collapsed over $400 (32%) to $840 on heavy volume</strong>. Of course, this is only a one-week low for the exuberant digital currency but still a significant plunge (as its smaller brethren <strong>Litecoin has collapsed 51% from its highs</strong>). Interestingly, this drops the price of Bitcoin in USD below the &#39;arb&#39;-based price of Bitcoin in China ($965). It seems, all coincidence aside, that the BIS infamous plunge-protection-team has been re-trained...</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user3303/imageroot/2013/11/20131201_BTC.jpg"><img height="556" src="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user3303/imageroot/2013/11/20131201_BTC_0.jpg" width="600" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>and as BTC collapsed, Gold rallied...</p>
<p><a href="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user3303/imageroot/2013/11/20131201_BTC1.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/images/user3303/imageroot/2013/11/20131201_BTC1_0.jpg" style="width: 600px; height: 313px;" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://bitcoinwisdom.com/"><em>Chart: Bitcoinwisdom</em></a></p>


</div>
